Subject: Re: [T2] '72 Spindle

My experience with this kind of thing leads me to believe that to switch
from the old to the new style front disk brake system requires switching the
caliper, steering knuckle, rotor, and backing plate.  The spindles are the
same, I believe.


> Q1:  Will a '79 bay's caliper and rotor fit on a '72 spindle?  I. e., can I
> simply swap out a '72 caliper/rotor with that from a '79.
> 
> Q2:  If not, how far back must I extract from the '79 to fit the system,
> bolt on, to a '72??
